text: Võ Thị Ánh Xuân (born 8 January 1970) is a Vietnamese politician. She became the Vice President of Vietnam in 2021. She was elected vice president on 6 April 2021 after winning 93.13% of votes in the National Assembly. ==References== Category:Vice presidents of Vietnam Category:1970 births Category:Living people
title: Võ Thị Ánh Xuân
